To fix tests and the "it never complains now about a missing import if it is not necessary" problem, I chose to hide this feature behind a `--require-used` flag.

On the subject of tests, I'm in the [Don't put logic in tests](http://googletesting.blogspot.com/2014/07/testing-on-toilet-dont-put-logic-in.html) camp. There's a ton of logic and code, in addition to external dependencies. I tried to go a different direction for the tests I wrote. My hope is that future developers will be able to quickly and easily understand their purpose, without having to understand all the supporting pieces.

